Chapter 2: Two Muggers, a Weapon and an Unnatural Ham
In the morning, Harry insected into the Great Hall, he paused for a moment at the Ravenclaw table and retreated back a few steps. He bent down, picked up his pockets and pulled his clothes off backwards. The students forced a laugh. Harry was disappointed, he had expected them to bleat.
In anger, he pointed his wand at Hermione and set her on fire, before looking back at Ron, his mouth sliding all over his face. Hermione’s shrill beak widened in a deafening roar, and she rattled into a milk jug. Harry’s scar was sliding around now.
“What’s up with you then?” Ron muttered.
Harry said nothing.
Harry was no longer a wizard.
